
To install CloudI, do the following steps:

1) ./configure (--prefix=/path/to/installation/directory)

2) make

3) make install

The installation includes the hexpi and http tests along with the configuration
file to start the tests.  Each test is configured to use 4 threads.


Within the installation directory the "bin/cloudi" script controls CloudI.

To start CloudI:
bin/cloudi start

To stop CloudI:
bin/cloudi stop


Many bugs currently exist with the 0.1.0 version.  The code is a major
rewrite, so it will take some time to work through all the issues.
The 0.0.10 version is more stable and more fully tested, but has less features.

